en=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104oat1665702714863.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oat1665702714863.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oat1665702714863.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oat1665702714863\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Session Panel\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies a panel that is available for the duration of the application session, even if a panel has been specified for the current component, or a toolbar definition exists.\n </p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"oat1665702714863__table_d11816e1_d11817e1_d11818e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Expected Value:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Panel name. String of up to 32 characters. Supports Unicode.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Default Value:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oat1665702714863__section_ppk_rcj_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d232601e94\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"oat1665702714863__table_d11819e1_d11820e1_d11821e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Dynamic?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">No, but the panel can be shown or hidden using Gold <span class=\"ph keypress\">X</span> (^ATTRIBUTE).</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Dependencies:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">PanelType</span> initialization setting enables or disables\n                           the session panel and controls its position. When set to\n                              <code class=\"ph codeph\">No</code>, the session panel is disabled and cannot be shown\n                           or hidden.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oat1665702714863__section_agj_tcj_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d232601e152\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oat1665702714863__p_d100802e1_d100803e1_d100804e1\">The exact appearance of the session panel depends\n            on the platform. On Windows, it is possible to configure the location and appearance of\n            the session panel using initialization settings:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"oat1665702714863__ul_mg2_5cj_5wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oat1665702714863__li_d40667e1_d40668e1_d40669e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nlx1665702616810.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nlx1665702616810.html\" title=\"Enables or disables the session panel, and controls its position.\">PanelType</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oat1665702714863__li_d40670e1_d40671e1_d40672e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"avj1665702614940.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/avj1665702614940.html\" title=\"Specifies a style for the appearance of buttons and borders in the Uniface toolbar and panels.\">ButtonStyle</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oat1665702714863__li_d40673e1_d40674e1_d40675e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fbn1665702616587.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fbn1665702616587.html\" title=\"Determines the background color of panels.\">PanelColor</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oat1665702714863__p_d100808e1_d100809e1_d100810e1\">If the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">PanelType</span> setting is not\n            present, the session panel is displayed as a floating panel.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oat1665702714863__section_bm5_vcj_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d232601e203\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"oat1665702714863__ul_pbg_wcj_5wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oat1665702714863__li_d39617e1_d39618e1_d39619e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1705472567076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1705472567076.html\" title=\"An application shell is the first object that is executed when a Windows or character mode application is started. It determines how the application is initialized and the first form component that is displayed.\">Application Shells for Desktop Applications</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/byf1705583062647.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Panels</a><p>Panels are global objects that are typically used to create toolbars for form components and application shells. They contain buttons to execute structure editor functions and activate component operations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614941\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614941\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Session Panel Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Session Panel Specifies a panel that is available for the duration of the application session, even if a panel has been specified for the current component, or a toolbar definition exists. Expected Value: Panel name. String of up to 32 characters. Supports Unicode. Default Value: None Usage Dynamic? No, but the panel can be shown or hidden using Gold X (^ATTRIBUTE). Dependencies: PanelType initialization setting enables or disables the session panel and controls its position. When set to No , the session panel is disabled and cannot be shown or hidden. Description The exact appearance of the session panel depends on the platform. On Windows, it is possible to configure the location and appearance of the session panel using initialization settings: PanelType ButtonStyle PanelColor If the PanelType setting is not present, the session panel is displayed as a floating panel. Applies To Application Shells for Desktop Applications Related Links Panels Panels are global objects that are typically used to create toolbars for form components and application shells. They contain buttons to execute structure editor functions and activate component operations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}